# Design

## Unified UI color scale

All UI colors are defined in `src/app/globals.css` under "Unified UI color scale". Change the `--ui-*` variables there to experiment.

- **--ui-bg**: page background (darkest in dark mode, lightest in light mode).
- **--ui-frame**: panels/cards; use the `.frame` class.
- **--ui-elevated**: buttons, dropdowns, empty-state surfaces (one step above frames).
- **--ui-success**: success actions, winner shots, confirm. Tailwind: `bg-ui-success`, `text-ui-success`.
- **--ui-error**: delete, cancel, error shots. Tailwind: `bg-ui-error`, `text-ui-error`.

Body uses `--ui-bg` and `--foreground`. Prefer `bg-ui-elevated` for form controls and secondary surfaces.

## Frames and panels

- **No stroke** on cards/panels. Do not use borders for frame separation.
- Use the **`.frame`** class for all panels and cards. It sets the frame background color and a drop shadow (and rounded corners). Defined in `src/app/globals.css`.
- **`.frame-glass`** is kept in CSS for reference but should not be used in new UI.

## Colors

- **Accent** `#43D1A7`: optional CTA highlight. CSS variable `--accent`; Tailwind `text-accent`, `bg-accent`.
- **Shot-type colors** (charts, legends): `--shot-serve`, `--shot-clear`, etc. in `globals.css` and `SHOT_TYPE_HEX` in `src/lib/shot_chart_utils.ts`. Use for bar fills, donut segments, legends.

## Typography

- App font is set in `src/app/layout.tsx` (Outfit) and applied via `--font-sans`. Keep it consistent across pages.

## Reference

- Token definitions: `src/app/globals.css` (Unified UI color scale + shot-type tokens)
- Shot-type hex map: `SHOT_TYPE_HEX` in `src/lib/shot_chart_utils.ts`
